cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI

This paper discusses bibliometric methods and their use in research evaluation, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on journal coverage and biases in databases is particularly relevant to the sub-categories of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The analysis of biases in favor of certain fields and languages may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY), as well as social and information networks (cs.SI).
